{
  "texts": [
    "McKenzie et al. (2017) use three machine learning approaches, SVM, Least Absolute Shrinkage and Selection Operator (LASSO) and Boosted Regressor to predict the chances of survival based on sales and profit of the start-up companies.",
    "Böhm et al. (2017) suggests using techniques such as cluster analysis and SVM to predict the chances of survival.",
    "Start-ups can also be measured based on innovations or the company's level of projects.",
    "Innovations can be a turning point as they can lead to reaching new heights and economic growth of the firms.",
    "Kinne and Lenz (2021) proposed a method to look at the innovation perspective of the business to predict the start-up success."
  ]
}